$interpreted: Alliance Soldier: As is tradition, these golden ballots are for choosing the Alliance Beauty.
Alliance Soldier: We ask everyone to please write down the name of their selection before the end of the tournament and hand it back to us.
Maeok: What about the audience's ballots?
Alliance Soldier: They'll get them as they enter the arena.
Turtle Chieftain: Heh, what's even the point?
Turtle Chieftain: Not like anyone comes close to Chiyuki. She's a real looker, that one!
Wolf Chieftain: You're not lyin'! Her hair looks so smooth...
Ace: Ugh...
Maeok: Now, the Alliance Beauty can actually be a man or woman. We choose one every twenty years to symbolize the beauty of the Alliance itself.
Maeok: It's a bit of an antiquated tradition, I'm aware, but please save your jokes. We have ambassadors present, so let's all show some respect.
Wolf Chieftain: Of course we respect the Alliance Beauty!
Turtle Chieftain: Maybe the arbiter's gettin' jealous. She ain't exactly a spring chicken herself!
Maeok: Excuse me—
Audience: Mom, look! Look up there!
Chiyuki: Ladies and gentlemen, the moment you've all been waiting for~ The Martial Arts Tournament is about to begin!
Chiyuki: I am extremely humbled for the opportunity to watch the tournament with all of you here today.
Chiyuki: As everyone knows, the Martial Arts Tournament is the pride and joy of the east, one that represents...
Chiyuki: ......
Audience: ...Didn't that sound kind of like a...
Chiyuki: ...One that represents the strength and unity of our unbreakable Alliance.
???: PPPFFFT—!!!!
Turtle Chieftain: ...Are my ears having problems, or did Miss Chiyuki just...?
Wolf Chieftain: Nope, I heard it too...
Chiyuki: ......
Chiyuki: Omigodomigodomigod this is so embarassing!! And I've only been eating fresh vegetables this whole week!!

Chiyuki: Is there something wrong with the stage, or... 
No... I'm already up here, I can't mess up now. I have to make the best of it.
Chiyuki: I'm Hanazono Chiyuki, the lonely star... I've got to keep rolling on...
Chiyuki: I can't let some... questionable noises ruin my reputation.
Chiyuki: I won't let this get in the way of my future as this Alliance's arbiter!
???: PPFFFFT—!!!!
Chiyuki: This time we have ten accomplished contestants holding their tribes' holy talismen.
Chiyuki: Let's wish them all good luck!
Audience: Oh my, I'm getting embarassed for her!
Chiyuki: (Stay focused! You're almost done, don't let this get to you...)
Chiyuki: Next we'll be dividing our contestants into groups, so please—
???: PFFT—PPPPPPFFFFTTTT!!!!
Innocent Child: —Mommy, is that pretty lady farting?
Chiyuki: I am not farting!
Loving Mother: No need to yell. Everyone farts, it's quite normal.
Chiyuki: But I'm... I'm not! It's not me! I don't... I don't...
Chiyuki: Just please, keep it down!
Puggi: Weird, I'm already off that boat, why am I still so dizzy?
Puggi: Paaanngg, where'd you go? Who am I? Where am I?
Audience: Haha! What's all this, now? Some kind of surprise show?

Puggi: Oh, everybody's watching me... 
Hold on... is this...
Puggi: I've waited for so long.
Puggi: Is this... Is this my debut?
Puggi: It's only natural the main character should lead into the final act.
Puggi: Ladies. And. Gentlemen~!
Puggi: The one and only Puggi is here!!
Puggi: Please, shower me with love and money!
Innocent Child: Look at that bird, mommy, he's funny!
Audience: Not bad! Who's next!?
Chiyuki: What... What kind of crude performance was that?
Chiyuki: No way he's upstaging me... I need to keep my reputation!
Audience: Hehe! Chiyuki really screwed the pooch on this one!
Loving Mother: Hahah~ Oh man, I'm laughing too much, I'm crying!
Puggi: Forget about the tournament! I'm the real hero! Vote for Puggi!
Pang: ...When Hestia came and asked me for help, I didn't quite believe her...
Puggi: Hiyaa...
Pang: You'll have to excuse my friend, he's a little slow.
Chiyuki: (Oh no, I can't have the audience realize something's off...)
Chiyuki: Thank you so much, Mr. Puggi, for that... colorful performance... Now it's time for us to form up teams~
Chiyuki: If each contestant would please pick up one ball from the ground,
Chiyuki: the color of which will determine your starting challenge!
Chiyuki: Wonderful! Now, what will their starting challenges be? You'll all just have to wait and see!
Chiyuki: One more thing—We are aware of the rumors that surviving members of the Insect Tribe are planning to stage an attack...
Tindoiimu: An attack!? Jihasaha and Tingko haven't gotten to them yet? Has something happened!?
Soohyeon: ...Tindoiimu, you haven't heard? My mom said that a lot of people died, on both sides...
Toyokuni: ...Yes, a great deal of civilian casualties.
Tindoiimu: ......
Soohyeon: Mom also said that the Alliance wouldn't be holding back anymore.
Toyokuni: I think that's enough, Soohyeon. Take her feelings into consideration.
Soohyeon: ...I-I'm sorry.
Tindoiimu: (Not holding back, huh? If they push the Alliance too hard, the whole tribe really might get wiped out...)
Tindoiimu: (...But who am I to tell my sister what to do? I want vengeance, too, but I've already given up my chance to return home...)
Chiyuki: But fear not! You are all safe and sound under the protection of the Alliance. Please just sit back, relax, and enjoy the tournament.
Chiyuki: Thank you all! I'll see you next time~
Innocent Child: Mommy, I want to vote for Puggi!
Loving Mother: Hah, I think I want to vote for him, too~
Annoyed Viewer: You know I originally wanted to vote for Chiyuki, but...
Perplexed Viewer: I know! Same here! That bird-thing really came out of left field, didn't he? I feel like I've got to vote for him.
Organiser: Good work today, Miss Chiyuki! We'll take care of things from here, you should go get some rest.
Chiyuki: Alright, thank you.
Chiyuki: ......
Chiyuki: ...What a disaster... stupid bird...

Chiyuki: So embarrassing!!! How could I lose to a bird!? I prepared for this for so long!!! 
Gyaaaaaaghh!!!
Chiyuki: It's all... It's all that bird's fault...
Chiyuki: Made me look like a joke...
Chiyuki: —That's it! I'm taking back my audience! My reputation! Or my name isn't Hanazono Chiyuki!
